h4. Problem Definition:

Fields that are set as hidden in the field configuration still appear as valid options in the "Issue Detail View" within the board settings in Software projects;
h4. Steps to Reproduce:
 # Create a software project;
 # Create a custom field for testing purposes. It can be of any type;
 # Make sure to not include this field in the screen associated with the issue type of your choice for that project;
 # In the field configuration scheme for that project, make sure to hide the recently created custom field;
 # Go to the board settings and select the "Issue Detail View";
 # Go to the specific field type section and click on the dropdown to show the available fields for it;

This behaviour is described as being expected in https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-18710; presumably the logic is the same in server, but this is confusing and inconsistent for users, and can be improved.

There already exists a Marketplace API endpoint that relays the latest Jira version, but it would be useful for Long Term Support releases as some instances stay exclusively within this line.

Example:
{code:java}
https://marketplace.atlassian.com/rest/2/products/key/jira/versions
{code}

It is difficult to click & read the stories in the backlog because they sometimes swap places based on small mouse or trackpad movements.  I would appreciate better animation and more margin of error when moving stories because I frequently have two to three stories reordered when reading through a list of 15 stories in a sprint.

 

{{As a project manager reading stories}}

{{I want to click through stories without accidentally reordering them }}

{{So that I can read story details when trying to think through a project}}

 

{{The story reorder feature is great but the UI implementation is too sensitive.  I would like to see more delay on the movement of the stories and a gap created where the story will drop when it is dropped.  I believe this will fix the issue.}}

